xpiation-al-kaffarah","tag-forgiveness-al-maghfirah","tag-health","tag-manners-adab","tag-sickness-al-marad","tag-trials-al-balaa","tag-women-al-nisa"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-9PI","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":23456,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/07\/12\/hadith-on-trials-sickness-expiation-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":37802,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Sickness cause by sins, but Allah holds back","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 12, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bara' ibn 'Azib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe veins and the eyes do not tremble with illness but due to sins, yet Allah repels even more.\u201d Source: al-Mu'jam al-S\u0323aghi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 1053 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0632\u0650\u0628\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23969,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/11\/02\/hardship-pain-expiation\/","url_meta":{"origin":37802,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Every discomfort an expiation for sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 2, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNothing afflicts a Muslim of hardship, nor illness, nor anxiety, nor sorrow, nor harm, nor distress, nor even the pricking of a thorn, but that Allah will expiate his sins by it.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5641, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40069,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/13\/expiation-complaining\/","url_meta":{"origin":37802,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Expiation of sins for not complaining to people","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah Almighty said: If I put My servant to trial and he does not complain of Me to his visitors, I will release him from his captivity, then I will replace his flesh and blood with\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41747,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/01\/17\/expiation-illness\/","url_meta":{"origin":37802,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Sickness: Expiation of sins for enduring illness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 17, 2024","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, when the Muslim falls ill, Allah Almighty inspires the angels, saying: O angels, I have detained My servant with My confinement. If I take his soul, he will be forgiven. If I heal his body,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19102,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/11\/sickness-fire-expiate-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":37802,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Fever: Sickness is fire from Allah to expiate sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, visited a man who was sick and he said, \u201cBe glad, for Allah has said: It is My fire that I afflict upon my sinful servant as his share in place of Hellfire.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2088 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40014,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/12\/kafarah-saqam\/","url_meta":{"origin":37802,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Allah expiates all sins with sickness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 12, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah will put His servant to trial with illness until that expiates every one of his sins.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n lil-Bayhaqi\u0304 9397 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0